Since Gradle 6.7, Gradle introduced the notion of [_toolchains_ for the JVM][1]. _Toolchains_ allow to define a JDK version to be used to compile/run a project, that is a JDK different than the one running gradle.

This is as easy as writing in the build script :


    java {
        toolchain {
            languageVersion = JavaLanguageVersion.of(15)
        }
    }

Gradle will look up the requested toolchain on usual standard local paths (and you can evn provide your own lookup location via the `org.gradle.java.installations.paths` property), and can eventually download it. It even support multiple OpenJDK vendors. Their [documentation][1] explains it all.

So for a multi-project setup, you can do something like :

    .
    ├── jdk11
    │&#160;&#160; ├── build.gradle
    │&#160;&#160; └── src
    ├── jdk16
    │&#160;&#160; ├── build.gradle
    │&#160;&#160; └── src
    ├── jdk17
    │&#160;&#160; ├── build.gradle
    │&#160;&#160; └── src
    ├── build.gradle
    ├── gradle.properties
    └── settings.gradle


* `settings.gradle`

    ```groovy
    rootProject.name = &#39;THE-project&#39;    
    include(&quot;jdk11&quot;, &quot;jdk16&quot;, &quot;jdk17&quot;)
    ```

* `build.gradle`

    ```groovy
    subprojects {
      apply(plugin: &quot;java-library&quot;) // or whatever applies to the sub-project
    
      // repositories, test, ...
    }
    ``

* `gradle.properties` the property is optional, it is only if additional lookup path are needed

    ```properties
    org.gradle.java.installations.paths=/path to panama jdk,/path to loom jdk,etc
    ```


* `jdk11/build.gradle`

    ```groovy
    java {
      toolchain {
        languageVersion = JavaLanguageVersion.of(11)
      }
    }
        
    tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {
      options.release.set(11)
    }
        
    // dependencies, etc.
    ```

* `jdk16/build.gradle`

    ```groovy
    java {
      toolchain {
        languageVersion = JavaLanguageVersion.of(16)
      }
    }
        
    tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {
      options.release.set(16)
    }
        
    // dependencies, etc.
    ```

* `jdk17/build.gradle`

    ```groovy
    java {
      toolchain {
        languageVersion = JavaLanguageVersion.of(17)
      }
    }
        
    tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {
      options.release.set(17)
      options.compilerArgs = [&#39;--add-modules=jdk.incubator.foreign&#39;,
                              &#39;--enable-preview&#39;,
                              &#39;-Xlint:preview&#39;]
    }
        
    // dependencies, etc.
    ```

