If you want to know when the `space` key is being held, you should use two events.

1) On `keyPressed` set your held `boolean` to `true`
2) on `keyReleased` set your held `boolean` to `false`

Here is a small example:

```java
AtomicBoolean spaceHeld = new AtomicBoolean(false);

KeyboardFocusManager.getCurrentKeyboardFocusManager().addKeyEventDispatcher(ke -&gt;
{
	switch (ke.getID())
	{
		case KeyEvent.KEY_PRESSED:
			if (ke.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_SPACE)
			{
				spaceHeld.set(true);
			}
			break;

		case KeyEvent.KEY_RELEASED:
			if (ke.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_SPACE)
			{
				spaceHeld.set(false);
			}
			break;
	}
	return false;
});
```

